<div class="post-content">

<h2>Daytime Gameplay: A Full Crafting Adventure</h2>
<p>The day sections play like a proper Chipper and Sons sequel. You plant trees, water them (pro tip: spam the W key to water faster), chop them down for wood, and use that wood to craft structures from blueprints. The game gives you new recipes each day, and as you progress, you unlock automation: Chipo-Mats that generate wood planks passively, rock farms that produce stones, and frog sheds that create gifts automatically.</p>

<p>The map expands as the story advances. Day 1 keeps you at the lumber yard, but from Day 2 onward you gain access to meadows, a town, a beach, underwater areas, and more. Along the way you'll encounter varied minigames — serving food and drinks, fishing, a Chipper-themed whack-a-mole — and several boss fights that use the watering can as your weapon. From Poler, an alien tree defender, to a massive metal bird on an oil rig and a submarine boss, the encounters keep surprising you throughout.</p>

</div>

